title: Holmes added to President's Cup roster
text:
Holmes added to President's Cup roster Posted: Fri 2:58 PM, Oct 02, 2015 / Headlines List / Article 
LEXINGTON, Ky. (WKYT) - Former UK All-American J.B. Holmes has been added to the 2015 President’s Cup roster, replacing Jim Furyk, who will miss the event because of an injury. 
United States captain Jay Haas picked Holmes as Furyk’s replacement. 
The 33-year-old Holmes had a sensational season, highlighted by a win in April’s Shell Houston Open. Holmes finished the year with a fourth-place finish in Chicago and an eighth-place finish in Atlanta. 
The President’s Cup begins Oct. 8 at the Jack Nicklaus Golf Club Korea in Incheon, South Korea.
